    "caption": "Can't fly, doesn't need to — nothing can catch this bird on the ground.",
    "shortDescription": "Ostriches are the largest birds alive, and they can sprint at over seventy kilometers per hour — faster than a racehorse at full gallop. They only have two toes on each foot, with one enormous inner toe that acts like a hoof for pushing off the ground. Their long powerful legs can also deliver a kick that can kill a lion. Fun fact: Ostriches have eyes bigger than their brains — and those eyes are the largest of any land animal."
